Five WAGs experience the reality of life behind the World 
Cup gloss by working in some of the poorest, most 
deprived neighbourhoods in South Africa. The WAGs fly

their job is to work as foster mothers to children orphaned 
by AIDS. But for one of them the desperately poor conditions
